# Context Log Rule

- When the user shares background, causes, intent, constraints, rationale, or project context, append a concise summary to `docs/context-log.md`.
- Treat this as always-on workspace behavior, even if the user does not explicitly say "record this" each time.
- Never overwrite prior entries; only append new dated entries.
- Prefer short structured summaries over raw transcript dumps.
- If the content is ambiguous, ask a brief clarification question before recording.
- Do not record secrets, tokens, passwords, or other sensitive values verbatim.
